Hmmm.  A monk trains all his life for one on one battle.  A warrior's life is training on the battle field.  If you know anything about heavy armor and mobility, you would know that a body trained to defend against blows via avoiding them is better armor than heavy plate any day.  The heavy armor was made for those instances in the heat of combat of 1000+ vs 1000+ that you just couldn't see every blow coming and having that armor was just the thing that could make a hasty poorly timed blow turn into a dent in the armor instead of a chunk out of your backside.<br>
<br>
<br>
Monks are fine as they are.  We should be better face to face tanks than a warrior in many situations.  But... the defensive discipline, avoidance discipline are what set warriors up to have the best job of all.  Even if it's only for 3 minutes, they are the center of attention.  They are the focus of the raid.  And then to complain about someone else doing something you think you should ONLY do well?  Get a grip baby warriors.  Once they give monks weapons with slow procs or all the cool effects then you can complain.<br>
